DeveloperName.description: The unique name of the record in the API. This name can contain only underscores and alphanumeric characters, and must be unique in your org. It must begin with a letter, not include spaces, not end with an underscore, and not contain two consecutive underscores. This field is automatically generated, but you can supply your own value if you create the record using the API.

Label.description: This name is used to refer to the big object in the user interface. Available API version 41.0 and later.

ManageableState.description: Indicates the manageable state of the specified component that is contained in a package: beta deleted deprecated deprecatedEditable installed installedEditable released unmanaged

MasterLabel.description: Master label for the Index. This internal label doesnâ€™t get translated.

NamespacePrefix.description: A unique string to distinguish this type from any others.

SobjectType.description: The type of standard object that this record type is derived from. In this case, the parent big object.

Type.description: The type of index. Valid values are PRIMARY or SECONDARY.
